Package: footBayes
Type: Package
Title: Fitting Bayesian and MLE football models
Version: 0.1.0
Author: Leonardo Egidi
Maintainer: Leonardo Egidi <legidi@units.it>
Description: This is the first package allowing for the estimation,
             visualization and prediction of the most well-known 
             football models: double Poisson, bivariate Poisson,
             Skellam, student_t. The package allows Hamiltonian
             Monte Carlo (HMC) estimation through the underlying Stan
             environment and Maximum Likelihood estimation (MLE, for 
             'static' models only).
License: GPL-2
Depends: R (>= 3.1.0)
Imports: rstan (>= 2.18.1), reshape2, ggplot2, bayesplot, matrixStats,
         extraDistr, parallel, metRology, dplyr, engsoccerdata, numDeriv
LinkingTo: StanHeaders (>= 2.18.0), rstan (>= 2.18.1), BH (>= 1.66.0),
        Rcpp (>= 0.12.0), RcppEigen (>= 0.3.3.3.0)
Encoding: UTF-8
LazyData: true
RoxygenNote: 7.1.2
VignetteBuilder: knitr
Suggests: 
    testthat, knitr, rmarkdown
BuildManual: yes
